Mean System Size (mss): The mean number of customers or transactions. Also known as the average number of customers or transactions in the system.
Mean Response Time (mrt): The average number of customers or transactions in the system divided by the flow rate (throughput).
Mean Queue Size (mqs): the average number of customers or transactions in the queue waiting to be transmitted.
Mean Waiting Time (mwt) - Average time a customer or transaction waits for transmission
